# Backend workflow and validation

After **any backend code change** (in `apps/api/` or its tests), follow this flow. Run all commands from **`apps/api/`** (and ensure `uv` is on PATH; see testing-and-environment rule if not).

## Flow

1. **Make code changes** (app code or tests).
2. **Write tests** (unit and/or integration as needed).
3. **Run and debug tests:** `uv run pytest tests/ -v` — fix until all pass.
4. **Run lint and debug:**  
   - `uv run ruff check .`  
   - `uv run ruff format --check .` (or `uv run ruff format .` to fix)  
   - `uv run mypy app`  
   Fix any reported issues.
5. **Run pre-commit and debug:** `uv run pre-commit run --all-files` — fix any failing hook until all pass.

Always run pre-commit (`uv run pre-commit run --all-files`) on BE code changes **after tests are successful** so the commit stays clean.